    "lesson_content_markdown":  "# The \u0027Was Doing\u0027 Past\n\nWe use the **Past Continuous** to talk about an action that was middle in progress at a past time. This shows us the action was happening right then.\n\n### 1. Formula: Past Be Verb + Doing Word (-ing)\n\nTo make this tense, you need **two** parts:\n\n**1. The correct Past Be Verb**\n- **I, He, She, It** (one person) use **was**\n- **You, We, They** (many people) use **were**\n\n**2. The Doing Word with -ing**\n- Example: **read** â†’ **reading**\n- Example: **study** â†’ **studying**\n\n### 2. Examples:\n- At 10:00 AM yesterday, I **was studying** in the library.\n- The students **were eating** lunch when I arrived.\n- It **was raining** when class finished.\n\n### 3. When to use it?\n\n- To show someone was middle in their activity.\n- To describe the background of a story.\n- **Example**: She **was sitting** in the park when the bird flew over.\n\n---",
